\r\nng is the pronunciation of vowel &quot;au&quot; in &quot;sauH&quot;. One pronunciation &lt;/span&gt;&lt;=\r\nspan&gt;is somewhat close to &quot;o&quot; in &quot;doctor&quot;. One pronunciation is closer to &quot;=\r\navu&quot;. If you &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;phonologically &lt;/span&gt;analyze and experimen=\r\nt with the vriddhi sandhi\n rule (a + e =3D ai, a + o =3D au), you will real=\r\nize that the former pronunciation is closer to truth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div styl=\r\ne=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 13.3333px; font-family: arial,helvetic=\r\na,sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nb=\r\nsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 13.3333px; fo=\r\nnt-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-=\r\nstyle: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you formally studied linguistics and know &quot;vowel t=\r\nrapezium&quot;, u is at the top of the back and o is below it. The &quot;au&quot; sound is=\r\n below &quot;o&quot; and above &quot;a&quot; - half the way in between. The way some people pro=\r\nnounce it (&quot;savuhu&quot;), they are actually saying 3 aksharas/syllables (sa-vu-=\r\nhu) for what is supposed to be just one!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: r=\r\ngb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 13.3333px; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;=\r\n background-color: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/d=\r\niv&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0,\n 0, 0); font-size: 13.3333px; font-family: a=\r\nrial,helvetica,sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-style: norma=\r\nl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;=\r\n&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=\r\n=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 13.3333px; font-family: arial,helvetica=\r\n,sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbs=\r\np;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 13.3333px; fon=\r\nt-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-s=\r\ntyle: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like I always say, correct pronunciation is only 1% im=\r\nportant. Don&#39;t intentionally mis-pronounce when you know what is correct. H=\r\nowever, don&#39;t worry about what you are not sure of and do your best. Intent=\r\nion, sincerity and surrender are far more important than pronunciation. The=\r\nre may be mantras (e.g. Veda mantras) that work magically just with correct=\r\n pronunciation, but there is\n nobody now who can pronounce them perfectly. =\r\nSo forget about technicalities and inculcate sincerity and devotion.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/s=\r\npan&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13px;=\r\nfont-family:arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;background-color:transparen=\r\nt;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrology &=\r\namp; Spirituality Resources: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;=\r\nhttp://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;d=\r\niv style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13px;font-family:arial, helvetica,=\r\n clean, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;-------=\r\n-&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote style=3D&quot;border-left: 2px solid rgb(1=\r\n6, 16, 255); margin-left: 5px; margin-top: 5px; padding-left: 5px;&quot;&gt;  &lt;div =\r\nstyle=3D&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div=\r\n style=3D&quot;font-family: times new roman, new york, times, serif; font-size: =\r\n12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1